PN,37510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1777050358
OL,3,CDoctor told Calocane he could kill
OL,4,Csomeone years before Nottingham attacks
OL,6,FJust weeks after being discharged for
OL,7,Fthe first time on June 17 2020,
OL,8,FCalocane stopped taking his anti-
OL,9,Fpsychotic medication.
OL,11,FHis mother, Celeste Calocane, had
OL,12,Fconcerns that he was released from
OL,13,Fhospital too early, the inquiry heard.
OL,15,FHe was detained under mental health
OL,16,Flaws three more times before he
OL,17,Fcarried out the fatal attacks in 2023.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G10/11
